For both of us.

242
00:23:26,283 --> 00:23:28,513
What do you think of the course so far?

243
00:23:28,686 --> 00:23:30,916
To be honest, I don't know
what to make of it.

244
00:23:31,088 --> 00:23:32,715
XAVIER:
I suspected as much.

245
00:23:32,890 --> 00:23:36,883
Tell me, Michael, do you believe in sin?

246
00:23:37,061 --> 00:23:40,428
Yeah, I just don't necessarily believe
the devil makes us do it.

247
00:23:40,898 --> 00:23:43,298
He that committeth sin is of the devil.

248
00:23:44,068 --> 00:23:46,366
Then that'd be all of us, wouldn't it?

249
00:23:46,537 --> 00:23:48,869
And if we're all of the devil,
how do we fight him?

250
00:23:50,774 --> 00:23:55,006
Tomorrow, I recommend you take
your doubts for a walk around Rome.

251
00:23:55,779 --> 00:23:58,873
You can pay a visit
to an old friend of mine.

252
00:23:59,249 --> 00:24:00,716
Father Lucas?

253
00:24:00,884 --> 00:24:03,045
He's Welsh. Jesuit.

254
00:24:03,220 --> 00:24:05,916
His methods are a little less orthodox.

255
00:24:06,090 --> 00:24:08,217
Studied under
Father Carmine De Filippis.

256
00:24:08,392 --> 00:24:11,589
MICHAEL: I don't know what that means.
- It means he knows his stuff.

257
00:24:11,929 --> 00:24:16,696
He'll be happy to provide you with
the kind of proof you seem to need.

258
00:24:17,401 --> 00:24:19,631
Excuse me, I have a Mass to say.

259
00:25:00,611 --> 00:25:03,239
[BELL TOLLING]

260
00:25:11,855 --> 00:25:15,882
[CATS MEOWING]

261
00:25:45,122 --> 00:25:46,248
[MEOWS]

262
00:25:46,423 --> 00:25:48,414
Jesus.

263
00:25:48,592 --> 00:25:50,287
[MAN SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

264
00:25:51,528 --> 00:25:54,292
MICHAEL: Father Lucas?
- Yes?

265
00:25:54,731 --> 00:25:56,926
Hi. I'm Michael Kovak.

266
00:25:57,101 --> 00:26:00,764
- Oh. You're the American.
- Yeah.

267
00:26:01,171 --> 00:26:03,537
- You don't like cats?
- Not particularly.

268
00:26:03,707 --> 00:26:06,676
Welcome to Rome.
It's infested with cats.

269
00:26:06,844 --> 00:26:09,039
I've tried giving them names
but it's pointless.

270
00:26:09,213 --> 00:26:13,013
A cat won't come no matter what
you call it. They do as they please.

271
00:26:14,384 --> 00:26:16,352
Anyway, welcome.

272
00:26:20,157 --> 00:26:22,057
Make sure they don't come in.

273
00:26:23,694 --> 00:26:25,252
MICHAEL:
No. Hey, hey.

274
00:26:28,732 --> 00:26:30,700
Father Xavier tells me you're troubled.

275
00:26:30,868 --> 00:26:33,359
I don't think Father Xavier
explained the situation.

276
00:26:33,537 --> 00:26:35,698
He explained it well enough.

277
00:26:35,873 --> 00:26:37,602
I've arranged for you to meet someone.

278
00:26:37,774 --> 00:26:39,241
[KNOCKING]

279
00:26:39,409 --> 00:26:41,468
Speak of the devil.

280
00:26:46,016 --> 00:26:48,576
[LUCAS SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

281
00:26:49,720 --> 00:26:51,551
[ADRIANA & ROSARIA SPEAKING
IN ITALIAN]

282
00:26:53,957 --> 00:26:57,085
[IN ITALIAN] God bless you, Father,
thank you for seeing us.

283
00:26:57,261 --> 00:26:59,889
LUCAS [IN ITALIAN]:
There's no need to thank me.

284
00:27:02,566 --> 00:27:05,057
Put it in the kitchen.

285
00:27:06,503 --> 00:27:08,232
[BOTH SPEAK IN ITALIAN]

286
00:27:08,405 --> 00:27:09,895
LUCAS:
Sit down.

287
00:27:13,911 --> 00:27:15,503
ROSARIA [IN ITALIAN]:
Have you fed them?

288
00:27:15,679 --> 00:27:18,079
LUCAS:
No, they don't need feeding.

289
00:27:19,183 --> 00:27:23,483
ROSARIA:
Lucia. Gabriella. Dante. Federico.

290
00:27:23,820 --> 00:27:25,879
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

291
00:27:30,494 --> 00:27:32,086
ROSARIA:
Where's Hermione?

292
00:27:32,629 --> 00:27:33,994
LUCAS:
Come now.

293
00:27:34,164 --> 00:27:35,529
ROSARIA:
No. I want to see Hermione.

294
00:27:35,699 --> 00:27:37,758
After. Come.

295
00:27:45,108 --> 00:27:47,576
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

296
00:27:52,282 --> 00:27:56,082
[IN ENGLISH] If you wanna watch, you have
to help me. I'll need to absolve you first.

297
00:27:56,253 --> 00:27:57,652
MICHAEL:
Help with what?

298
00:27:57,821 --> 00:27:59,948
The exorcism. What do you think?

299
00:28:00,123 --> 00:28:02,819
Or you can stay down here
with her aunt.

300
00:28:03,393 --> 00:28:04,951
That could be fun.

301
00:28:05,128 --> 00:28:06,925
It's up to you.

302
00:28:07,197 --> 00:28:11,133
Whatever you do, don't address the girl
directly, no matter what she says.

303
00:28:11,301 --> 00:28:13,360
And if I ask you to hold her down...

304
00:28:13,537 --> 00:28:17,234
...it's best you grab her arms
from behind...

305
00:28:17,407 --> 00:28:19,739
...and try keeping her
in a seated position.

306
00:28:19,910 --> 00:28:22,378
The spirit is pretty devious.
Hasn't shown itself yet.

307
00:28:22,546 --> 00:28:24,707
- The spirit?
LUCAS: Yes. Spirit.

308
00:28:26,650 --> 00:28:28,982
Demon. The devil.

309
00:28:29,152 --> 00:28:32,315
If it hasn't shown itself,
how do you know she's possessed?

310
00:28:32,522 --> 00:28:34,956
All right, give me something,
anything that's yours.

311
00:28:36,994 --> 00:28:38,791
Put it in this.

312
00:28:39,162 --> 00:28:40,356
What is it, a dollar bill?

313
00:28:40,530 --> 00:28:42,691
Come on, do it. Quickly.
It's for your benefit.

314
00:28:43,867 --> 00:28:45,562
What else?

315
00:28:46,870 --> 00:28:48,735
Oh, yes. It's Michael, isn't it?

316
00:28:49,239 --> 00:28:52,470
I absolve you of any sins you may
have committed now or in the past...

317
00:28:52,643 --> 00:28:54,941
...in the name of the Father,
Son and Holy Spirit.

318
00:28:55,112 --> 00:28:57,876
- Amen.
- All right, come on.

319
00:28:59,650 --> 00:29:03,518
Oh, yes, one other thing. If it does manifest,
don't even look into the girl's eyes.

320
00:29:03,687 --> 00:29:06,952
Whatever you do, do not address it.
Do not speak to it. It's the devil.

321
00:29:07,124 --> 00:29:09,183
- Leave that to me. Do you understand?
- Cool.

322
00:29:09,359 --> 00:29:10,986
- Do you understand?
- Yeah, I get it.

323
00:29:11,161 --> 00:29:12,719
Well, just say so.

324
00:29:12,896 --> 00:29:15,387
Bow your head, keep praying
and good luck.

325
00:29:48,965 --> 00:29:50,694
LUCAS [IN ITALIAN]:
How are you?

326
00:29:51,034 --> 00:29:52,626
The same.

327
00:29:52,903 --> 00:29:54,871
LUCAS:
Have you eaten?

328
00:29:58,108 --> 00:30:00,440
What about your baby?

329
00:30:01,578 --> 00:30:03,876
You need to eat.

330
00:30:04,948 --> 00:30:06,643
[IN ENGLISH]
Okay.

331
00:30:08,685 --> 00:30:10,312
<i>Um...</i>

332
00:30:10,754 --> 00:30:13,587
[IN ITALIAN]
What's happened since Tuesday?

333
00:30:13,957 --> 00:30:17,825
ROSARIA: It won't stop now.
Even when I sleep it talks.

334
00:30:17,994 --> 00:30:19,985
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

335
00:30:20,163 --> 00:30:21,528
[CHUCKLES]

336
00:30:22,132 --> 00:30:23,827
[IN ENGLISH]
Okay.

337
00:30:24,634 --> 00:30:26,864
Now she's gonna guess what's in the bag.

338
00:30:27,170 --> 00:30:29,297
Rosaria?

339
00:30:29,940 --> 00:30:31,601
[IN ITALIAN]
See the bag?

340
00:30:31,775 --> 00:30:33,299
[ROSARIA SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

341
00:30:33,477 --> 00:30:36,173
Tell me what's in it.

342
00:30:37,514 --> 00:30:38,947
How could I know that?

343
00:30:39,116 --> 00:30:41,209
Then I want you to guess.

344
00:30:44,154 --> 00:30:45,178
I don't know.

345
00:30:45,355 --> 00:30:47,346
Clear your mind and guess.

346
00:30:47,524 --> 00:30:49,992
It's not a test. Just guess.

347
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:51,286
I don't want to.

348
00:30:51,461 --> 00:30:53,361
I'm ordering you to guess! Guess!

349
00:31:01,638 --> 00:31:05,870
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

350
00:31:08,812 --> 00:31:10,575
[IN ENGLISH]
Show her.

351
00:31:20,690 --> 00:31:22,453
There you are.

352
00:31:22,626 --> 00:31:24,753
Knowledge of the unknowable.

353
00:31:25,128 --> 00:31:26,993
It's the quickest test for possession.

354
00:31:27,164 --> 00:31:30,327
The devil is working in and through her
right now.

355
00:31:32,135 --> 00:31:33,568
Okay.

356
00:31:39,176 --> 00:31:40,700
<i>Uh...</i>

357
00:31:40,877 --> 00:31:43,368
[IN ITALIAN]
Did it tell you what was in the bag?

358
00:31:43,547 --> 00:31:44,673
[ROSARIA SPEAKING
IN ITALIAN]

359
00:31:44,848 --> 00:31:46,577
Is it talking now?

360
00:31:46,750 --> 00:31:48,445
What's it saying?

361
00:31:50,454 --> 00:31:52,854
Disgusting things.

362
00:31:53,023 --> 00:31:56,356
It's important you tell me.

363
00:32:00,730 --> 00:32:03,665
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

364
00:32:08,872 --> 00:32:11,500
LUCAS:
Has it told you its name yet?

365
00:32:13,810 --> 00:32:15,437
Do you know its name?

366
00:32:15,612 --> 00:32:16,772
Tell me its name.

367
00:32:16,947 --> 00:32:18,471
Tell me now.

368
00:32:33,396 --> 00:32:35,830
[LUCAS SPEAKING IN LATIN]

369
00:32:52,983 --> 00:32:55,543
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

370
00:32:57,220 --> 00:32:58,812
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

371
00:32:59,523 --> 00:33:00,956
[IN ENGLISH]
In!

372
00:33:04,761 --> 00:33:05,955
[MICHAEL SPEAKING IN LATIN]

373
00:33:06,129 --> 00:33:08,859
LUCAS [IN ITALIAN]: I can't talk now,
I'm in the middle of something.

374
00:33:13,803 --> 00:33:16,363
[ROSARIA GRUNTING]

375
00:33:16,540 --> 00:33:19,134
[LUCAS SPEAKING IN LATIN]

376
00:33:23,046 --> 00:33:26,277
ROSARIA [IN ITALIAN]:
Shut up, shut up.

377
00:33:26,616 --> 00:33:28,777
Shut up, priest.

378
00:33:29,519 --> 00:33:31,544
You must not touch me.

379
00:33:31,955 --> 00:33:33,252
You are disgusting.

380
00:33:33,523 --> 00:33:35,150
Keep your dirty hands off me.

381
00:33:35,325 --> 00:33:37,259
Shut up! You must not speak.

382
00:33:37,427 --> 00:33:38,792
Don't touch me!

383
00:33:39,062 --> 00:33:40,620
Go away, priest. Go away!

384
00:33:40,797 --> 00:33:43,095
You stink, you are disgusting.

385
00:34:09,225 --> 00:34:10,852
Rosaria.

386
00:34:12,062 --> 00:34:13,222
Rosaria.

387
00:34:14,331 --> 00:34:16,322
Open your mouth.

388
00:34:16,866 --> 00:34:18,493
[LUCAS SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

389
00:34:19,135 --> 00:34:20,329
How do you feel?

390
00:34:20,503 --> 00:34:22,562
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

391
00:34:27,911 --> 00:34:29,344
LUCAS [IN ENGLISH]:
Okay.

392
00:34:37,721 --> 00:34:39,689
Okay, that's it.

393
00:34:49,399 --> 00:34:51,367
MICHAEL:
Really? That's it?

394
00:34:51,534 --> 00:34:54,264
Well, what'd you expect?
Spinning heads, pea soup?

395
00:34:58,441 --> 00:35:01,137
Spiritual liberation can take months,
sometimes years.

396
00:35:01,645 --> 00:35:03,875
So she's still possessed?

397
00:35:04,047 --> 00:35:05,173
Yeah.

398
00:35:05,348 --> 00:35:08,010
I know you don't believe me, <i>but...</i>

399
00:35:09,386 --> 00:35:10,910
Tell me...

400
00:35:12,222 --> 00:35:16,591
...does a thief or a burglar turn on the
lights when he's robbing your house? No.

401
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:20,992
He prefers you to believe
that he's not there.

402
00:35:21,164 --> 00:35:24,156
Like the devil. He prefers you
to believe that he doesn't exist.

403
00:35:24,334 --> 00:35:30,068
It gets complicated when no proof of
the devil is somehow proof of the devil.

404
00:35:31,041 --> 00:35:32,633
Yeah.

405
00:35:42,218 --> 00:35:45,051
The interesting thing
about skeptics, atheists...

406
00:35:45,221 --> 00:35:50,215
...is that we're always looking
for proof, certainty.

407
00:35:50,393 --> 00:35:53,453
The question is, what on earth
would we do if we found it?

408
00:35:53,630 --> 00:35:55,257
- "We"?
- Oh, yes.

409
00:35:55,432 --> 00:35:58,993
There are times when I experience
a total loss of faith.

410
00:35:59,169 --> 00:36:01,831
Days, months when I don't know
what the hell I believe in.

411
00:36:02,005 --> 00:36:05,338
God or the devil,
Santa Claus or Tinker Bell.

412
00:36:05,642 --> 00:36:07,405
But...

413
00:36:08,645 --> 00:36:10,806
...you know, I'm just a man.

414
00:36:10,980 --> 00:36:13,346
I'm a weak man. I have...

415
00:36:14,651 --> 00:36:16,551
...no power.

416
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:22,758
Yet there's something that keeps
digging and scraping away inside me.

417
00:36:23,293 --> 00:36:26,319
Feels like God's fingernail.

418
00:36:26,529 --> 00:36:29,692
And finally I can take
no more of the pain...

419
00:36:29,866 --> 00:36:34,269
...and I get shoved out
from the darkness...

420
00:36:34,437 --> 00:36:36,530
...back into the light.

421
00:36:37,874 --> 00:36:40,069
Something like that.

422
00:36:41,778 --> 00:36:44,144
[SPEAKS IN LATIN]

423
00:36:46,349 --> 00:36:48,317
Anyway, enough philosophizing
for one day.

424
00:36:48,485 --> 00:36:52,945
If you have any more questions,
you know where to find me.

425
00:36:55,325 --> 00:36:58,089
I got my eye on you. What you doing?

426
00:37:12,308 --> 00:37:15,141
[CHATTERING]

427
00:37:23,987 --> 00:37:26,319
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

428
00:37:38,802 --> 00:37:40,963
[HORNS HONKING]

429
00:37:50,046 --> 00:37:52,446
You're in Rome and you go to McDonald's?

430
00:37:52,615 --> 00:37:53,639
Oh, hey.

431
00:37:54,184 --> 00:37:57,711
Come on. Let me buy you
an Italian coffee.

432
00:38:01,758 --> 00:38:04,852
ANGELINA: Where were you today?
Xavier kicked you out, didn't he?

433
00:38:05,028 --> 00:38:08,122
Yeah, I've plea-bargained down
from being burned at the stake.

434
00:38:08,331 --> 00:38:10,925
So you're just vacationing now
on the Church's dime?

435
00:38:11,100 --> 00:38:13,261
Yeah, and yours.

436
00:38:14,137 --> 00:38:17,470
Seriously, why are you taking the course?

437
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:20,131
Why are you?
Are they recruiting nuns for exorcists?

438
00:38:21,778 --> 00:38:22,972
"Nuns"?

439
00:38:24,614 --> 00:38:27,549
I'm sorry, I just naturally <i>assumed...</i>

440
00:38:27,717 --> 00:38:29,947
Yeah, naturally.

441
00:38:32,956 --> 00:38:35,584
Well, if you're not a nun,
why are you taking the course?

442
00:38:36,893 --> 00:38:40,852
I'm a journalist. I'm covering
the course for an article.

443
00:38:41,030 --> 00:38:43,999
I see. And I thought
you were just buying me a coffee.

444
00:38:44,367 --> 00:38:48,303
There's a lot of interest in this.
A lot of debate.

445
00:38:51,107 --> 00:38:52,665
Look...

446
00:38:53,309 --> 00:38:55,402
...I know you saw Father Lucas today.

447
00:38:56,079 --> 00:38:59,742
I've been trying to get an interview
with him, but he's been reluctant.

448
00:38:59,916 --> 00:39:01,781
What is it you want?

449
00:39:02,385 --> 00:39:05,013
- I'd love to know what you saw.
- You're asking me to spy?

450
00:39:05,188 --> 00:39:07,952
No, I'm asking you to report
your own experiences.

451
00:39:09,058 --> 00:39:10,423
Listen...

452
00:39:11,261 --> 00:39:13,991
...I'm just interested in the truth.

453
00:39:14,931 --> 00:39:16,865
Seems like you are too.

454
00:39:19,269 --> 00:39:23,968
XAVIER: Just as there is a hierarchy
of angels, ranked in ascendant order...

455
00:39:24,140 --> 00:39:27,576
...so, too, is the realm of evil ranked.

456
00:39:27,744 --> 00:39:29,905
And just as each angel has a name...

457
00:39:30,079 --> 00:39:32,274
...so, too, does every demon.

458
00:39:32,448 --> 00:39:36,077
Beelzebub, Leviathan, Ba'al.

459
00:39:36,252 --> 00:39:38,482
These are some of the names
we look for...

460
00:39:39,055 --> 00:39:41,580
...when performing an exorcism.

461
00:39:41,758 --> 00:39:43,419
[PEOPLE GASPING]

462
00:39:46,529 --> 00:39:48,895
Just bear with me for a moment.

463
00:39:51,935 --> 00:39:56,531
Well, I think we should leave it there
and pick it up tomorrow. Thank you.

464
00:40:04,180 --> 00:40:06,171
Michael, how's my old friend Lucas?

465
00:40:06,349 --> 00:40:08,283
MICHAEL:
He's unorthodox.

466
00:40:08,451 --> 00:40:10,282
XAVIER:
No exorcism is orthodox.

467
00:40:10,453 --> 00:40:13,581
MICHAEL: He's treating a pregnant girl
that I believe needs psychiatric care.

468
00:40:13,756 --> 00:40:14,984
XAVIER:
You believe?

469
00:40:15,158 --> 00:40:17,456
Father Lucas has been doing this
longer than anyone I know.

470
00:40:17,627 --> 00:40:19,458
MICHAEL:
I'm telling you because I'm concerned.

471
00:40:19,629 --> 00:40:20,823
It's not uncommon...

472
00:40:20,997 --> 00:40:24,057
...to be overly concerned for the subject
in one's first exorcism.

473
00:40:24,233 --> 00:40:27,691
You have to see that
it is the demon that's in pain.

474
00:40:28,438 --> 00:40:30,872
Trust me. Father Lucas gets results.

475
00:40:31,040 --> 00:40:32,371
At what cost?

476
00:41:12,448 --> 00:41:15,281
[KNOCKING]

477
00:41:21,224 --> 00:41:24,250
Oh. What can I do for you?

478
00:41:26,095 --> 00:41:27,119
LUCAS:
Rosaria.

479
00:41:27,296 --> 00:41:28,991
[IN ITALIAN]
You remember this man?

480
00:41:29,165 --> 00:41:31,497
He was sent by the Vatican.

481
00:41:32,502 --> 00:41:35,471
I want you to answer his questions.

482
00:41:36,472 --> 00:41:38,235
Hi.

483
00:41:38,408 --> 00:41:42,970
It was terrible to see you
go through your suffering.

484
00:41:43,212 --> 00:41:47,273
This is unimportant. Just nod.

485
00:41:47,450 --> 00:41:49,350
MICHAEL:
Do you remember any of it?

486
00:41:49,886 --> 00:41:53,686
He wants to know if you remember things
when the devil takes over your body.

487
00:41:55,525 --> 00:41:57,550
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

488
00:42:01,931 --> 00:42:06,800
LUCAS [IN ENGLISH]:
