How did you enter her?

731
00:59:55,937 --> 00:59:57,871
With her father's seed.

732
00:59:58,039 --> 01:00:01,941
- So you remember being raped?
LUCAS: Don't address it directly.

733
01:00:02,110 --> 01:00:07,776
[IN GREEK] When the devil has nothing
better to do, he rapes his children.

734
01:00:08,750 --> 01:00:09,774
I don't understand.

735
01:00:09,951 --> 01:00:11,612
[SPEAKS IN GREEK]

736
01:00:11,786 --> 01:00:14,653
[LAUGHING]

737
01:00:16,291 --> 01:00:18,452
You know how to swear
in every language?

738
01:00:18,627 --> 01:00:22,529
ROSARIA [IN LATIN]: Therefore let us
go down and confound their tongue...

739
01:00:22,697 --> 01:00:25,257
...that they may not understand
one another's speech.

740
01:00:26,234 --> 01:00:28,065
MICHAEL:
You know the Bible well.

741
01:00:28,236 --> 01:00:30,898
We know it very well.

742
01:00:35,810 --> 01:00:36,970
Very clever.

743
01:00:37,145 --> 01:00:39,010
[IN ENGLISH]
Don't patronize me, doubter!

744
01:00:39,447 --> 01:00:42,507
It is I who chose you.

745
01:00:43,084 --> 01:00:45,644
- Why do you call me "doubter"?
ROSARIA: Because it's true.

746
01:00:46,555 --> 01:00:49,023
A liar knows a liar.

747
01:00:51,660 --> 01:00:53,958
Are you a liar, Rosaria?

748
01:00:54,129 --> 01:00:56,290
What is it you want me to believe?

749
01:00:56,464 --> 01:00:58,159
There's nothing to believe.

750
01:00:59,334 --> 01:01:01,529
Then there is no devil
and you're not possessed?

751
01:01:01,836 --> 01:01:04,930
You fear me, mortal!

752
01:01:06,741 --> 01:01:09,301
How can I fear you if you don't exist?

753
01:01:31,800 --> 01:01:33,859
You think you outsmarted him?

754
01:01:35,070 --> 01:01:37,197
That's not the devil.

755
01:01:37,672 --> 01:01:40,197
It's just a very, very sick girl.

756
01:01:41,276 --> 01:01:44,109
She doesn't need a priest,
she needs a shrink.

757
01:01:46,414 --> 01:01:50,145
He still has you fooled, hasn't he?

758
01:01:54,522 --> 01:01:56,956
You forgot your bag of tricks.

759
01:02:01,796 --> 01:02:04,230
LUCAS:
He's a deceiver, Michael.

760
01:02:07,335 --> 01:02:09,735
He's a deceiver.

761
01:02:50,773 --> 01:02:54,300
[MONITOR BEEPING]

762
01:03:54,403 --> 01:03:56,871
[ALARM BEEPING]

763
01:04:06,048 --> 01:04:07,709
[ALARM BEEPING]

764
01:04:07,884 --> 01:04:09,852
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN ITALIAN
OVER SPEAKER]

765
01:04:15,191 --> 01:04:17,682
[IN ITALIAN]
Hold on. Hold on, Rosaria.

766
01:04:18,694 --> 01:04:21,492
[PEOPLE CHATTERING IN ITALIAN]

767
01:04:27,303 --> 01:04:30,761
MAN 1 [IN ITALIAN]:
<i>This is a tragedy. How could this happen?</i>

768
01:04:31,307 --> 01:04:35,937
Who worked here today?
I want to talk with everyone.

769
01:04:39,181 --> 01:04:41,376
MAN 2 [IN ITALIAN]:
Tell me about the mother.

770
01:04:42,351 --> 01:04:46,253
[IN ITALIAN] There was internal bleeding,
massive hemorrhaging.

771
01:04:49,258 --> 01:04:51,123
We did everything in our power...

772
01:04:51,294 --> 01:04:54,559
...but unfortunately
we couldn't save her or her baby.

773
01:05:05,441 --> 01:05:06,908
MICHAEL:
What now?

774
01:05:07,743 --> 01:05:09,506
Oh, nothing.

775
01:05:09,912 --> 01:05:11,846
It's finished.

776
01:05:12,481 --> 01:05:15,973
He took a life.
That's what he wants, ultimately.

777
01:05:17,320 --> 01:05:20,118
He'll probably find someone else.

778
01:05:23,626 --> 01:05:26,390
You should go home, get some rest.
You've had a hard night.

779
01:05:26,562 --> 01:05:28,393
Yeah.

780
01:05:31,667 --> 01:05:33,692
Are you okay?

781
01:05:36,439 --> 01:05:37,804
I failed her.

782
01:05:38,774 --> 01:05:41,265
You did what you thought was best.

783
01:05:42,244 --> 01:05:43,939
Yeah.

784
01:05:50,353 --> 01:05:52,184
I gotta go.

785
01:05:54,924 --> 01:05:56,323
Take care of yourself.

786
01:06:02,431 --> 01:06:04,490
You're a good man, Michael.

787
01:06:05,868 --> 01:06:08,132
You have a good soul.

788
01:06:08,971 --> 01:06:10,939
Defend it.

789
01:06:11,173 --> 01:06:12,936
Guard it.

790
01:06:13,743 --> 01:06:15,711
Cherish it.

791
01:06:18,314 --> 01:06:21,442
Oh, God. Oh, God.

792
01:06:21,617 --> 01:06:24,848
[SOBBING]

793
01:06:44,040 --> 01:06:46,065
- Hey.
- Thanks for coming.

794
01:06:46,242 --> 01:06:48,870
You picked a perfect day for it.

795
01:06:49,045 --> 01:06:50,444
I appreciate you doing this.

796
01:06:51,580 --> 01:06:54,879
- No names.
- No names. Promise.

797
01:06:55,051 --> 01:06:57,952
There's no way she touched the baby
because she was restrained.

798
01:06:58,120 --> 01:06:59,747
That's right.

799
01:07:00,156 --> 01:07:02,181
What do you make of that?

800
01:07:04,060 --> 01:07:05,425
It's confounding.

801
01:07:05,861 --> 01:07:08,329
That's the story.
It's yours to interpret as you will.

802
01:07:08,497 --> 01:07:10,988
You can call me
if you have any questions.

803
01:07:11,167 --> 01:07:12,293
Thank you.

804
01:07:16,639 --> 01:07:18,869
What changed your mind?

805
01:07:19,175 --> 01:07:20,608
To do this?

806
01:07:21,444 --> 01:07:24,072
I just needed to tell someone.

807
01:07:26,682 --> 01:07:28,309
ANGELINA [IN VOICE-OVER]:
<i>So let me get this straight.</i>

808
01:07:28,684 --> 01:07:32,347
You ran away from home
and chose a life of celibacy?

809
01:07:32,888 --> 01:07:36,119
- How bad could home be?
- It sounds stupid when you say it like that.

810
01:07:36,292 --> 01:07:39,284
It sounds stupid
because it doesn't add up.

811
01:07:39,829 --> 01:07:42,627
Are you saying you never felt a calling?

812
01:07:43,632 --> 01:07:45,600
My mother...

813
01:07:45,801 --> 01:07:48,668
...she used to say
she felt the hand of God on me.

814
01:07:49,872 --> 01:07:50,998
Did you feel it?

815
01:07:52,408 --> 01:07:54,308
I wanted to.

816
01:07:57,346 --> 01:08:00,247
- So how did you end up in all this?
- It's a long story.

817
01:08:00,416 --> 01:08:02,077
We're not going anywhere,
so come on.

818
01:08:04,386 --> 01:08:08,220
My parents committed my brother
to a mental institution when he was 19.

819
01:08:10,126 --> 01:08:11,923
He was so tormented.

820
01:08:12,094 --> 01:08:15,461
He said he heard voices
telling him to do things.

821
01:08:16,065 --> 01:08:18,932
He used to tell me
it was the devil speaking to him.

822
01:08:22,705 --> 01:08:25,902
Sometimes he would tell me
what the devil said.

823
01:08:29,411 --> 01:08:32,073
And sometimes the things he said
would come true.

824
01:08:34,049 --> 01:08:35,573
It frightened me.

825
01:08:36,285 --> 01:08:38,776
He frightened me.

826
01:08:40,856 --> 01:08:46,192
I know it sounds terrible, but it's just
easier when I don't think about him.

827
01:08:46,362 --> 01:08:50,059
[WHISTLES BLOWING]

828
01:09:23,532 --> 01:09:27,263
YOUNG MICHAEL: <i>Hail Mary, full of grace.</i>
<i>The Lord is with thee.</i>

829
01:09:27,436 --> 01:09:29,199
<i>Blessed art thou among women...</i>

830
01:09:29,371 --> 01:09:33,364
<i>... and blessed is the fruit</i>
<i>of thy womb, Jesus.</i>

831
01:09:33,542 --> 01:09:35,066
<i>Holy Mary...</i>

832
01:09:35,611 --> 01:09:37,909
<i>... mother of God...</i>

833
01:09:38,080 --> 01:09:41,743
<i>... pray for us sinners now</i>
<i>and at the hour of our death.</i>

834
01:09:41,917 --> 01:09:43,680
<i>Amen.</i>

835
01:10:22,558 --> 01:10:24,583
[KNOCKING]

836
01:10:26,695 --> 01:10:29,391
I'm sorry to wake you, Michael.

837
01:10:30,733 --> 01:10:32,758
I thought it best to tell you myself.

838
01:10:33,168 --> 01:10:35,136
It's your father.

839
01:10:36,839 --> 01:10:38,568
And he hasn't regained consciousness?

840
01:10:38,741 --> 01:10:41,175
MAN [OVER PHONE]:
<i>No. The stroke was massive.</i>

841
01:10:41,343 --> 01:10:44,403
<i>He could stabilize</i>
<i>or he could stay like this.</i>

842
01:10:44,580 --> 01:10:45,604
I see.

843
01:10:45,781 --> 01:10:49,217
<i>I'm sorry. There isn't much more</i>
<i>I can tell you at this point.</i>

844
01:10:55,357 --> 01:10:57,416
I'm sorry, Michael.

845
01:10:57,593 --> 01:11:00,221
I'll include him in my prayers.

846
01:11:03,699 --> 01:11:05,530
We can help arrange your travel.

847
01:11:07,903 --> 01:11:09,598
Thank you.

848
01:12:38,894 --> 01:12:41,362
You gotta be fucking kidding me.

849
01:12:45,234 --> 01:12:48,965
WOMAN [ON TV]: <i>Airlines are warning</i>
<i>passengers to expect more delays...</i>

850
01:12:49,138 --> 01:12:52,164
<i>... even when the dust from</i>
<i>the volcano in Iceland has settled.</i>

851
01:12:52,341 --> 01:12:56,778
<i>Tonight, the ash plume has shut the</i>
<i>airports of 22 countries on the continent...</i>

852
01:12:56,945 --> 01:13:01,746
<i>... with Italy and Switzerland among</i>
<i>the latest to close their airspace.</i>

853
01:13:01,917 --> 01:13:02,941
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

854
01:13:03,118 --> 01:13:05,518
<i>Thousands of passengers are stranded,</i>
<i>with some being told...</i>

855
01:13:05,687 --> 01:13:07,882
<i>... it could be a week</i>
<i>before they get another flight.</i>

856
01:13:08,057 --> 01:13:09,615
- <i>Once the ash clears...</i>
- I need a room.

857
01:13:09,792 --> 01:13:12,352
- <i>... a backlog of flights...</i>
- [IN ENGLISH] No problem.

858
01:13:12,528 --> 01:13:16,624
<i>... will mean further disruption.</i>
<i>Valerie Rigg, Egetsa Coverage.</i>

859
01:13:16,799 --> 01:13:19,666
I'm calling to check
on my father's condition.

860
01:13:19,835 --> 01:13:21,462
Istvan Kovak.

861
01:13:21,637 --> 01:13:24,299
K-O-V-A-K.

862
01:13:24,473 --> 01:13:25,997
WOMAN [OVER PHONE]:
<i>I'll connect you.</i>

863
01:13:30,179 --> 01:13:33,171
[LINE RINGING]

864
01:13:35,984 --> 01:13:39,317
ISTVAN [OVER PHONE]: <i>Michael.</i>
- Yeah, yeah. It's Michael.

865
01:13:39,888 --> 01:13:41,617
<i>I'm scared.</i>

866
01:13:41,790 --> 01:13:44,315
It's okay. Dad, you're okay.

867
01:13:44,493 --> 01:13:48,486
<i>No. Something happened.</i>

868
01:13:49,331 --> 01:13:52,528
- It's okay, Dad.
- <i>Where are you?</i>

869
01:13:53,335 --> 01:13:54,734
<i>I wish you were here.</i>

870
01:13:54,903 --> 01:13:59,203
I'll be home soon.
Something happened with my flight.

871
01:14:00,309 --> 01:14:02,277
<i>Where am I?</i>

872
01:14:03,345 --> 01:14:05,370
You're in the hospital.

873
01:14:05,814 --> 01:14:07,907
[ISTVAN GRUNTS]

874
01:14:08,517 --> 01:14:10,678
What is it, Dad?

875
01:14:12,888 --> 01:14:14,549
Dad?

876
01:14:15,190 --> 01:14:17,317
<i>They're hurting me.</i>

877
01:14:17,493 --> 01:14:19,154
Who?

878
01:14:20,362 --> 01:14:21,886
Dad?

879
01:14:22,064 --> 01:14:24,794
MAN [OVER PHONE]: <i>Mr. Kovak?</i>
- Yeah.

880
01:14:24,967 --> 01:14:27,527
- <i>It's Dr. Vorachian.</i>
- Yes.

881
01:14:28,036 --> 01:14:32,496
<i>Mr. Kovak, I'm afraid</i>
<i>I've got some very bad news.</i>

882
01:14:32,674 --> 01:14:35,108
<i>Your father passed away this afternoon.</i>

883
01:14:37,846 --> 01:14:39,780
Uh, what?

884
01:14:40,582 --> 01:14:46,043
<i>Your father died this afternoon.</i>
<i>I'm very sorry, Mr. Kovak.</i>

885
01:14:46,622 --> 01:14:49,386
Well, that's impossible. <i>I...</i>

886
01:14:49,558 --> 01:14:52,391
I was just speaking with him, just now.

887
01:14:52,561 --> 01:14:57,055
<i>Mr. Kovak, your father was</i>
<i>declared dead about six hours ago.</i>

888
01:14:57,232 --> 01:14:59,291
<i>I was a witness.</i>

889
01:14:59,968 --> 01:15:02,766
<i>I'm very sorry to have to tell you...</i>

890
01:15:13,315 --> 01:15:16,011
[SOBBING]

891
01:15:31,533 --> 01:15:35,128
PRIEST: "Whoever lives by believing in me
will never die."

892
01:15:35,304 --> 01:15:38,273
Lord have mercy, Christ have mercy...

893
01:15:39,107 --> 01:15:41,132
...Lord have mercy.

894
01:15:41,310 --> 01:15:45,644
Eternal rest grant unto her, O Lord,
and let perpetual light shine upon her.

895
01:15:45,814 --> 01:15:47,475
<i>May she rest in peace.</i>

896
01:16:03,165 --> 01:16:05,099
ROSARIA [IN VOICE-OVER]:
<i>Doubter!</i>

897
01:16:24,086 --> 01:16:25,644
[WOMAN GASPS]

898
01:16:33,662 --> 01:16:37,223
[WOMAN CACKLING]

899
01:17:08,864 --> 01:17:10,798
ISTVAN [IN VOICE-OVER]:
<i>Michael.</i>

900
01:17:12,934 --> 01:17:15,232
ROSARIA:
<i>A liar knows a liar.</i>

901
01:17:15,404 --> 01:17:17,838
[WOMAN CACKLING]

902
01:17:18,006 --> 01:17:19,837
ISTVAN:
<i>Michael, they're hurting me.</i>

903
01:17:20,342 --> 01:17:21,366
MICHAEL:
Dad?

904
01:17:21,543 --> 01:17:23,374
ISTVAN: <i>I'm scared.</i>
MICHAEL: Hey.

905
01:17:27,783 --> 01:17:30,217
Wait! Dad!

906
01:17:30,419 --> 01:17:32,410
ISTVAN: <i>Where are you?</i>
ROSARIA: <i>Radre.</i>

907
01:17:32,587 --> 01:17:33,679
<i>Radre.</i>

908
01:17:37,092 --> 01:17:38,525
ISTVAN:
<i>Don't worry.</i>

909
01:17:39,628 --> 01:17:40,720
<i>The pain is gone.</i>

910
01:17:49,938 --> 01:17:52,634
ROSARIA:
<i>There's nothing to believe.</i>

911
01:17:59,715 --> 01:18:01,706
[MULE SNORTS]

912
01:18:47,429 --> 01:18:49,158
MICHAEL:
<i>I don't know what's going on.</i>

913
01:18:49,798 --> 01:18:53,199
I'm hallucinating. I'm seeing things,
I'm hearing things.

914
01:18:53,368 --> 01:18:56,496
I can't explain it.

915
01:18:56,671 --> 01:18:58,969
I don't even know what I'm doing here.

916
01:18:59,141 --> 01:19:01,200
ANGELINA [OVER PHONE]:
<i>Michael, what happened?</i>

917
01:19:01,376 --> 01:19:03,503
Look, I need your help.

918
01:19:03,678 --> 01:19:06,306
I feel like I'm going insane.

919
01:19:06,948 --> 01:19:08,438
Can you come meet me?

920
01:19:21,596 --> 01:19:25,430
FRANCESCA [IN ITALIAN]: <i>He's feeling</i>
<i>much better since the Father prayed for him.</i>

921
01:19:28,603 --> 01:19:30,127
Did Father send you?

922
01:19:31,106 --> 01:19:32,403
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

923
01:19:32,574 --> 01:19:36,010
The other day I saw her son
whisper something to her.

924
01:19:37,045 --> 01:19:38,603
I need to know what it was.

925
01:19:39,948 --> 01:19:42,883
[IN ITALIAN] Your son whispered
something to you the other day.

926
01:19:44,486 --> 01:19:46,977
He's a baby.
He doesn't know what he's saying.

927
01:19:47,155 --> 01:19:50,522
ANGELINA: Please, it's very important
that you tell us.

928
01:19:52,794 --> 01:19:54,386
Please.

929
01:19:58,033 --> 01:20:00,934
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

930
01:20:06,508 --> 01:20:08,408
ANGELINA [IN ENGLISH]:
He said...

931
01:20:11,513 --> 01:20:13,378
...your father was going to die.

932
01:20:19,488 --> 01:20:21,547
Who told him that?

933
01:20:25,293 --> 01:20:27,454
[ANGELINA SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

934
01:20:29,865 --> 01:20:32,231
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

935
01:20:37,906 --> 01:20:39,373
He says you know.

936
01:20:39,541 --> 01:20:42,066
He says you've seen it too.

937
01:20:42,444 --> 01:20:44,378
Seen what?

938
01:20:45,580 --> 01:20:46,945
The demon.

939
01:20:47,883 --> 01:20:49,578
The mule.

940
01:20:53,522 --> 01:20:56,389
ANGELINA: Where are you going?
- My father died last night.

941
01:20:56,558 --> 01:20:57,616
What did you say?

942
01:21:00,529 --> 01:21:02,895
I said, my father died...

943
01:21:03,164 --> 01:21:04,188
...last night.

944
01:21:05,400 --> 01:21:07,334
Oh, God.

945
01:21:08,336 --> 01:21:09,735
That's awful. I'm so sorry.

946
01:21:10,705 --> 01:21:12,866
How did that kid know?

947
01:21:14,843 --> 01:21:17,209
I need to talk to Lucas.

948
01:21:53,048 --> 01:21:55,812
[IN ITALIAN]
Bless my dolly, Father?

949
01:21:57,519 --> 01:21:58,747
Hm?

950
01:22:00,722 --> 01:22:02,849
[LUCAS SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

951
01:22:24,479 --> 01:22:26,913
[GIRL SCREAMS]

952
01:22:31,820 --> 01:22:34,118
[GIRL CRYING]

953
01:22:56,144 --> 01:22:57,736
Father?

954
01:22:58,546 --> 01:22:59,570
Father.

955
01:23:02,250 --> 01:23:04,548
Let's get you inside.

956
01:23:05,320 --> 01:23:08,289
[LUCAS SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

957
01:23:30,545 --> 01:23:34,003
- I don't want to lie down.
- Okay.

958
01:23:35,216 --> 01:23:36,774
Then what were you doing out there?

959
01:23:36,951 --> 01:23:38,885
LUCAS:
Huh?

960
01:23:39,054 --> 01:23:41,181
I said, what were you doing out there?

961
01:23:47,495 --> 01:23:49,486
LUCAS [IN VOICE-OVER]:
<i>I'm not sure.</i>

962
01:23:49,864 --> 01:23:54,062
<i>I found myself walking and I...</i>
<i>I think...</i>

963
01:23:54,402 --> 01:23:57,303
I think I did something awful.
It was terrible.

964
01:23:57,472 --> 01:24:01,067
I can't pray any longer because
I'm no longer in a state of grace...

965
01:24:01,242 --> 01:24:03,710
<i>... and prayer is our only salvation.</i>

966
01:24:03,878 --> 01:24:05,038
It's your only salvation.

967
01:24:05,213 --> 01:24:09,445
And remember this:
It knows you, it knows all your sins.

968
01:24:11,586 --> 01:24:13,781
